# NadBurn — api-server environment variables
#
# These are read at startup by the Express server. They are NEVER bundled
# into the frontend, so this is the right place for paid-API secrets.

# ----- Allowed browser origins (required when frontend is on Vercel) -----
#
# The api-server's CORS / CSRF guard only accepts requests whose `Origin`
# header is in its allowlist. The allowlist is built from these env vars
# (any of them may be a comma-separated host list, no scheme):
#
#   REPLIT_DEV_DOMAIN  — set automatically in Replit dev preview
#   REPLIT_DOMAINS     — set automatically on Replit Deployments
#   PUBLIC_APP_DOMAIN  — additional host(s) you publish the frontend to
#
# When the frontend lives on Vercel at nadburn.xyz, set this so the
# api-server trusts cross-origin requests from there:
#
#   PUBLIC_APP_DOMAIN="nadburn.xyz"
#
# Multiple hosts are comma-separated, e.g. "nadburn.xyz,staging.nadburn.xyz".
# Do NOT include `https://` — the server prepends it.
#
# Setting this also flips the session cookie from `SameSite=Strict` to
# `SameSite=None; Secure` so the cookie survives cross-site fetches from
# the frontend, and configures the OIDC login/logout flow to redirect users
# back to the first allowed frontend origin instead of the api-server's own
# host. Leaving this UNSET keeps the original same-origin (Strict) behavior.

# ----- Uniswap Trading API (required for chain 143 recovery) --------------
#
# Used by routes/uniswap.ts to proxy quote / approve / swap calls for V4
# recovery on Monad mainnet. Get a key at https://hub.uniswap.org or use
# the playground key from https://api-docs.uniswap.org for development.
#
# UNISWAP_TRADING_API_KEY="..."

# Optional override of the upstream base URL — almost never needed.
# UNISWAP_TRADING_API_BASE="https://trade-api.gateway.uniswap.org/v1"

# Optional override of the Origin header we forge when calling Uniswap.
# Uniswap's Trading API rejects requests without an Origin, and our
# server-to-server fetch doesn't set one by default, so we forge
# https://app.uniswap.org. Override only if Uniswap allowlists you on a
# different origin.
# UNISWAP_TRADING_API_ORIGIN="https://app.uniswap.org"

# ----- Blockvision (required for Monad mainnet auto-detect) ---------------
#
# Used by routes/explorer.ts on chain 143 to list a wallet's ERC-20
# holdings on Monad mainnet (Blockscout has no public API there). Sign up
# at https://blockvision.org for a free API key.
#
# BLOCKVISION_API_KEY="..."

# ----- Session ------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Random 32+ byte string used to sign session cookies. Replit auto-creates
# this for you in dev; set it explicitly for production deploys.
#
# SESSION_SECRET="..."
